(Walker, 1851)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="B8BD2A067F0FFFFDFD855CDAFD45FA6C" box="[556,763,1444,1469]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,569,1262]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[167,1419,555,1273]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 20–25. Habitus and male genitaliae of Aphrophoridae of Iran recorded as pests in orchards (already published in: Mozaffarian &amp; Wilson 2015): 20–21. Aphrophora alni, 20. Habitus, 21. Male genitalia, a: aedeagus, dorsal view, b: stylus, laterl view; 22–23. Philaenus spumarius, 22. Habitus, 23. Male genitalia, a: aedeagus, ventral view, b: stylus, lateral view, c: anal tube ventral view; 24–25. Poophilus costalis, 24. Habitus, 25. Male genitalia, a: aedeagus, lateral view, b, c: stylus, lateral view, d. anal tube, lateral view, e. genital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455391/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="484">Figs 24 and 25a–e</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
